BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:bRl1d0lzhJtG-u2cJWPab
SUMMARY:SY 101: Basics of Electronic Audio
DTSTAMP:20260326T010713Z
DTSTART:20260416T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:Interested in learning more about synthesizers? In this informa
	tive 2-hour workshop\, our instructor will provide you with a brief histor
	y of synthesis and a detailed breakdown of Basic Subtractive Patching!\n\n
	*The use of a laptop and headphones are required to participate in this cl
	ass. You will need to download the free software VCV Rack. Vera has a limi
	ted amount of laptops that we can provide on a first-come-first-serve basi
	s to our members. If you do have your own laptop\, we would appreciate if 
	you used your own\, so we can provide laptops to those who may not have on
	e. If you would like to request a laptop\, please email yewon@theveraproje
	ct.org. You will also need to download a couple files for this workshop. T
	hese files will be sent 24 hours before the class.\n\nhttps://link.dice.fm
	/E7347b6c5c21\n\nFrom The Vera Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/E7347b6c5c21
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:vera-project
CATEGORIES:The Vera Project
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Gl0HkbBAM0b7NgUY6-aqk
SUMMARY:LS 101: Basics of Live Sound
DTSTAMP:20260326T010713Z
DTSTART:20260416T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:Basics of Live Sound is a 2-hour introduction to live audio eng
	ineering and an orientation to Vera Project’s methods and equipment. Topic
	s covered include an introduction to microphones and mic placement\, signa
	l paths\, stands\, cables\, DI’s\, snake\, sub-snakes and etiquette for wo
	rking with bands. This class is designed for both the novices and experts 
	of all ages and will give an overview of signal flow and setting up small 
	PAs\, in addition to the basic requirements for being part of the Vera sou
	nd team at shows. Discover why the accommodating\, open minded “Vera Attit
	ude” of show production is appreciated worldwide!\n\nThis class is a prere
	quisite for advanced audio classes at Vera and Sound Runner shifts at Vera
	 Project show. Each Live Sound class unlocks new audio engineering volunte
	er shifts at Vera and eventually paid opportunities in and outside of the 
	venue. Become a volunteer at Vera to access other audio-related educationa
	l programs such as tours\, field trips\, and internships!\n\nhttps://link.
	dice.fm/m231e882bc33\n\nFrom The Vera Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/m231e882bc33
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:vera-project
CATEGORIES:The Vera Project
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:-i3Cv7c2usj8lwNtbnaak
SUMMARY:SP 101: Intro to VERA's Screen Print Studio
DTSTAMP:20260326T010713Z
DTSTART:20260416T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:This 2-hour\, comprehensive hands-on class teaches you all the 
	basics of screen printing at VERA’s screen printing studio: From hand-draw
	ing a stencil on transparency\, coating and burning a screen\, to pulling 
	your very first print! Get comfortable with Vera's shop layout\, equipment
	\, and culture. Learn techniques for creating screens\, terminology\, and 
	more to create 1-color projects in the print shop. Students will walk away
	 with the basic skills for screen printing 1-color paper prints\, and thei
	r own print of a special Vera design\, specific to the 101 class.\n\nThis 
	class is a prerequisite for 200-level classes at VERA\, as well as access 
	to Open Sessions to work on your own projects in VERA’s screen printing st
	udio.\n\nhttps://link.dice.fm/Sb24c5dacf8b\n\nFrom The Vera Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/Sb24c5dacf8b
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:vera-project
CATEGORIES:The Vera Project
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
